how can i get over being a people pleaser i am suffering from the disease to please it's hard to say no to friends boyfriends family co workers is it low self esteem before you answer anyone asking for your help take a second count in silence this is to keep you from immediately answering before you have time to think about the consequences of immediately saying' yes to the request you might get for your help when you answer instead of thinking you are hurting someone's feelings by saying no just think of yourself as a different person who is answering maybe a character from tv answering the same way someone else would say no tricks your mind into thinking that it isn't you who is turning down everyone it is that character who is doing it and get ready to be that character when you have to answer in a negative way to your friends you will eventually get it down and realize how little it matters to please everyone all the time you'll stop being taken advantage of and start being considered smart instead of a pushover Friends Shaggy dog story Utilitarianism One Tree Hill (TV series) Theory of conduct Alcoholics Anonymous Piccolo Junior Saga The Ashlee Simpson Show Sex and the City Kodocha Transactional analysis Aerial (dance move) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Memento (film) Socrates Obsessive-compulsive disorder Indian nationality law Oh My Goddess! Coming of Age (TNG episode) Boston Public Knots Landing Skat Tenshinhan Megan Griffin Ranma __ characters 2000 Australian Grand Prix A Course In Miracles Stuttering Jacen Solo Too Short a Season (TNG episode) Strategic management EastEnders Alignment (role-playing games) Saved by the Bell Rent (musical) Jean Grey Bernard Williams Humphrey Bogart Eddie Guerrero John Carter (ER) God Emperor of Dune Anorexia nervosa Honey and Clover The Silence of the Lambs Yuri Sakazaki Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Domestic violence Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Married... with Children Episodes of Lost 